GM Language Documentation (AnzerOS)

GM is a lightweight, declarative programming language for creating interactive apps directly in AnzerOS.

Features
Stability & Performance

Only redraws the current line while typing.

Full redraw happens only when necessary (scrolling, running apps).

Eliminates vertical flicker during typing.

Supported Commands
Command	Description
APP "NAME" "VERSION"	Defines a new application
WINDOW "TITLE" width height	Creates a window
LABEL x y "TEXT"	Adds static text
BUTTON x y width height "TEXT"	Adds a clickable button
RECT x y width height COLOR	Draws a colored rectangle
TEXTBOX x y width height	Adds a text input field
CHECKBOX x y "TEXT"	Adds a toggle checkbox
IMAGE x y width height	Displays an image
Colors

Hex codes: FF9955, etc.

Named colors: RED, GREEN, BLUE, YELLOW, ORANGE, PURPLE, WHITE, BLACK, GRAY

Interactive Preview

Click a CHECKBOX to toggle it.

Click a TEXTBOX to type.

Open saved Desktop files to run them in an App window without an IDE.

Example GM App
APP "MYAPP" "1.0"
WINDOW "APP" 220 120
LABEL 10 10 "HELLO"
TEXTBOX 10 30 100 16
CHECKBOX 10 55 "ENABLE"
BUTTON 10 80 80 16 "OK"
RECT 120 30 40 20 BLUE
IMAGE 120 60 40 20

This creates a window with a label, textbox, checkbox, button, rectangle, and image. Fully interactive inside AnzerOS.
